max
) and steeply sloping to PB (60–70°); DB straight, moderately sloping to postero-dorsal angulation (10–20°) with length increasing through ontogeny; ADB straight, long, with relatively constant length through ontogeny (37–45% of L), sloping toward AB with an angle ranging from 20° to 40°; AB large, relatively bairdiid in shape, with maximum of curvature at or slightly below mid-H; ventral margin long and sinuous; AVB steeply raised
